  "text": "Clustering coefficient depend on the underlying quality of the data to hand. Reguly and Breitkreutz et al. [CITATION_1] show that the higher-quality literature-curated interaction data can in fact provide more accurate predictions of the integrated network -for example in the prediction of protein complexes from physical interactions, or the Bayesian integration of multiple sourcesthan those obtained from high-throughput data alone. They also show that among the different methods of assessing interactions between genes and proteins, the literaturecurated data appear to be best predictors of shared Gene Ontology (GO) function or pathway, transcriptional coregulation, and tendency towards evolutionary conservation.",
